        <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"
                        ><lang/><w>*bṛz-ant-</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ira"
                                ><w>*barz-ant-</w></mentioned>, . Старое причастное образование на
                %iond%i( ← -%iant%i-) от основы %ibarz%i- ‘возвышаться’ (ср. аналогичные образования
                        <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tæssond"/>). В выражении %ibærz-k˳yvd ut%i „да
                будет ваше пиршество высоким (= благословенным)“ сохранилась краткая форма %ibærz%i.
                Рефлексы индоевропейского <mentioned xml:lang="ine"
                                        ><lang/><w>*bherǵh-</w><gloss><q>возвышаться</q></gloss></mentioned>
                обильно представлены в иранских и индоевропейских языках. Ближайшие соответствия:
                        <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>buland (←*bṛdant- ←
                        bṛzant-)</w></mentioned>), <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                                        ><lang/><w>bərəzant</w><gloss><q>высокий</q></gloss></mentioned>,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                        ><lang/><w>bṛhant-</w><gloss><q>великий</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>высокий</q></gloss></mentioned>, ’.<note n="1">
                        PUT NOTE HERE </note> Ср. также <mentioned xml:lang="ku"
                        ><lang/><w>barz</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="tly"
                                ><lang/><w>barz</w><gloss><q>высокий</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="tly"><w/><gloss><q>высоко</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
                        xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>burz</w></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="x-balochi"
                        ><lang/><w>burz</w><gloss><q>высокий</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="x-balochi"
                        ><w>burzag</w><gloss><q>возвышенность</q></gloss></mentioned>, (<bibl><ref
                                target="#ref_Зарубин._Бел."/><biblScope>I 52</biblScope></bibl>),
                        <mentioned xml:lang="xpr"
                        ><lang/><w>burz</w><gloss><q>высокий</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>*βarz</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                                ><w>*βarzāk(βrz, βrz'k)</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="kho"
                                ><lang/><w>bulysa(←*bṛza-)</w><gloss><q>длинный</q></gloss></mentioned>,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                        ><lang/><w>barəz-</w><gloss><q>высокий</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="ae"><w>barəzah-</w><gloss><q>высота</q></gloss></mentioned>, ,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="peo"><lang/><w>Bardiya</w></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="arc"
                        ><lang/><w>barjr</w><gloss><q>высокий</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="arc"><w>berj</w><gloss><q>высота</q></gloss></mentioned>, ,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="de"
                        ><lang/><w>Berg</w><gloss><q>гора</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="x-tchr"
                        ><lang/><w>pārk-</w><gloss><q>подыматься</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="x-tchr"><w>pärkär</w><gloss><q>длинный’</q></gloss></mentioned>, ,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="hit"
                        ><lang/><w>parkuš</w><gloss><q>высокий</q></gloss></mentioned>. — См. также
                        <ref type="xr" target="#entry_barz"/> ‘холм’, ‘куча’. Обозначения величины в
                осетинском почти все относятся к иранскому слою; см. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_styr"/> ‘большой’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_darǧ"/>
                ‘длинный’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fætæn"/> ‘широкий’, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_wæræx"/> ‘широкий’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bæzǵyn"/>
                                ‘толстый’.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II
                                82</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                                /><biblScope>20</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref
                                target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."/><biblScope>28</biblScope></bibl>. —
                                <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>20,
                        222</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
        <etym xml:lang="en">It traces back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"
                        ><lang/><w>*bṛz-ant-</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ira"
                                ><w>*barz-ant-</w></mentioned>, . An old participle derivate with
                %iond%i( ← -%iant%i-) from the stem %ibarz%i- ‘rise’ (cf. analogous derivations <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_tæssond"/>). In the expression %ibærz-k˳yvd ut%i
                "may your feast be high (= blessed)“ a short form %ibærz%i is found. The reflections
                of Indo-European <mentioned xml:lang="ine"
                                ><lang/><w>*bherǵh-</w><gloss><q>rise</q></gloss></mentioned> are
                widespread in Iranian and Indo-European languages. The closest correspondences are
                the following: <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>buland (←*bṛdant- ←
                        bṛzant-)</w></mentioned>), <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                                        ><lang/><w>bərəzant</w><gloss><q>high</q></gloss></mentioned>,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                        ><lang/><w>bṛhant-</w><gloss><q>great</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>high</q></gloss></mentioned>, ’.<note n="1"> PUT
                        NOTE HERE </note> Cf. also <mentioned xml:lang="ku"
                        ><lang/><w>barz</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="tly"
                                ><lang/><w>barz</w><gloss><q>high</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="tly"><w/><gloss><q>высоко</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
                        xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>burz</w></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="x-balochi"
                        ><lang/><w>burz</w><gloss><q>high</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="x-balochi"><w>burzag</w><gloss><q>height</q></gloss></mentioned>,
                                (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Зарубин._Бел."/><biblScope>I
                        52</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="xpr"
                                        ><lang/><w>burz</w><gloss><q>high</q></gloss></mentioned>,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>*βarz</w></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="sog"><w>*βarzāk(βrz, βrz'k)</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned
                        xml:lang="kho"
                        ><lang/><w>bulysa(←*bṛza-)</w><gloss><q>long</q></gloss></mentioned>,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                        ><lang/><w>barəz-</w><gloss><q>high</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="ae"><w>barəzah-</w><gloss><q>height</q></gloss></mentioned>, ,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="peo"><lang/><w>Bardiya</w></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="arc"
                        ><lang/><w>barjr</w><gloss><q>high</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="arc"><w>berj</w><gloss><q>height</q></gloss></mentioned>, ,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="de"
                        ><lang/><w>Berg</w><gloss><q>mountain</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="x-tchr"><lang/><w>pārk-</w><gloss><q>go
                        up</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="x-tchr"
                                        ><w>pärkär</w><gloss><q>long</q></gloss></mentioned>, ,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="hit"
                        ><lang/><w>parkuš</w><gloss><q>high</q></gloss></mentioned>. — Cf. also <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_barz"/> ‘hill’, ‘pile’. Almost all of the notions
                of height in Ossetic belong to Iranian layer; see <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_styr"/> ‘big’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_darǧ"/> ‘long’,
                        <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fætæn"/> ‘wide’, <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_wæræx"/> ‘wide’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bæzǵyn"/>
                                ‘fat’.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II
                                82</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                                /><biblScope>20</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref
                                target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."/><biblScope>28</biblScope></bibl>. —
                                <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>20,
                        222</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
